Sec. 7. (a) The state department, in consultation with the
Indiana board of pharmacy, the medical licensing board of
Indiana, the Indiana state board of nursing, and the office of the
attorney general shall develop and publish a report not later than
November 15 of each year concerning the oversight of drug
compounding during the preceding fiscal year.
(b) The report must include the following:
(1) A general assessment of the public health impact drug
compounding, including the benefits and risks presented by
compounding.
(2) The following data and information from the preceding
fiscal year:
(A) The number and type of professional licenses issued, by
